The paper discusses a statistical technique for analyzing co-occurrence data, which has applications in information retrieval and natural language processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions machine learning from text, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses a generalization of maximum likelihood model fitting, which could suggest that it belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
